The Vice President visited Cape Coast Castle in Ghana and reflected on the horrors that took place there during the transatlantic slave trade. He described the dungeons where men, women, and children were kept before being sold as slaves in the Americas and the Caribbean. He acknowledged the unknown number of lives lost during the journey and emphasized the importance of remembering and teaching this history. The Vice President also recognized the resilience of those who survived and their fight for freedom and justice. He concluded by expressing gratitude for their struggle and its impact on the world.